== 21st century revival ==
The ''Gallaic Revival Movement'' claims to be in the process of [[language revitalization|reviving]] the Gallaecian language, which it calls ''Gallaic''. It aims to [[linguistic reconstruction|reconstruct]] the Gallaecian language through [[comparative linguistics]], drawing from better-documented Celtic languages such as [[Old Irish]], supplemented by words from the Old Celtic Dictionary. One of the goals of the movement is the creation of an ''Atebivota Dictionary'' of Gallaecian words. The movement says that it is supported by the ''Liga C<U+00E9>ltiga Galaica'' (Gallaecian Celtic League). The ambition to revive the Gallaecian language seems to be related to a desire for recognition by pan-Celtic organizations such as the [[Celtic League (political organisation)|Celtic League]], which have a policy of only recognizing a nation as Celtic if it has a living Celtic language.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gallaicrevivalmovement.page.tl/|title=Gallaic Revival Movement|accessdate=11 May 2013}}</ref><ref>{{Wayback|url=http://gallaicrevivalmovement.spruz.com/|date=20121002063828|df=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://gallaic.com|title=Gallaic Revival|accessdate=11 May 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Old Celtic Dictionary|url=http://oldcelticdictionary.com/}}</ref> 

